      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-08T22:56:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This will be happening. The query above relies on global datastore indexes, they will get stale. It has been observed many times with Swarming. Relying on global indexes to be up-to-date is bad.\n\nEither the agent will need to keep retrying 404 for some time (and thus SEE 404 in the first place), or the entity structure need to change to avoid reliance on global indexes (for example by adding a VMHostname entity pointing to the VMKind entity).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 128,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 128,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "6e2fcbd863d57d6cffd153afc78472f8d7be12da",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "296afd41_9ddcc0aa",
        "filename": "gce/appengine/rpc/instances.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 128,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-09T22:06:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Wait why will it be happening? You mean if a new VM is brought online but the index isn\u0027t updated so the query incorrectly returns nothing for awhile? I think that\u0027s fine because it should have the same behavior as the Machine Provider agent, it will fail and chromebuild-startup.py will relaunch it until it doesn\u0027t fail.",
      "parentUuid": "284eda5c_604ee676",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 128,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 128,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "6e2fcbd863d57d6cffd153afc78472f8d7be12da",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "001a376e_2aec959f",
