    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "988bcda7_9b675cef",
        "filename": "gce/appengine/rpc/instances.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 157,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-08T22:56:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not a fan of this explicit check everywhere, it is very easy to forget to add for a new API method (and I think you\u0027ve already forgot to add it to Delete? It neither checks vmtoken.Has nor vmtoken.Hostname). \n\nIt would be much better to forbid access to VMs by default, and only allow it where it is needed. A good place to add this is in prpc prelude. Something like:\n\n// All methods listed here MUST check vmtoken.Hostname().\nvar vmAccessibleMethods \u003d []string{\n  \"Get\",\n}\n\nfunc vmAccessPrelude(...) ... {\n  if caller is in auth groups {\n    proceed()\n  }\n\n  if method in vmAccessibleMethods \u0026\u0026 vmtoken.Has(...) {\n    proceed()\n  }\n\n  permission_denied()\n}",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 157,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 157,
        "endChar": 20
      },
      "revId": "6e2fcbd863d57d6cffd153afc78472f8d7be12da",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
